When we consider possible errors for each genotype call, in each window, the probability of finding k times of genotype ‘B’ for each genotype follows a binomial distribution. The probability of observing k times of genotype ‘B’ in a sliding window of size n can be calculated separately as the following:5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
