				\begin{document}$${P}_{X}(k)={(}_{k}^{n})\times {(\frac{1+{E}_{X}}{2})}^{k}\times {(\frac{1-{E}_{X}}{2})}^{n-k}$$\end{document}PX(k)=(kn)×(1+EX2)k×(1−EX2)n−kwhere EA, EB, and EX are SNP error rates of the three genotypes. By incorporating the estimated proportions of three genotypes, the genotype with the maximum probability within the window is selected:8\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
